#Author: persist
#Abstract: how to convert a directory to *.img

1. create a raw image of the required size (use seek to creates a sparse file, which saves space)
$ dd if=/dev/null of=example.img bs=1M seek=10240

2. create a filesystem on it
$ mkfs.ext4 -F example.img

3. mount it
$ mkdir /mnt/example
$ mount -t ext4 -o loop example.img /mnt/example

4. copy files to /mnt/example

5. umount it

